Hub sends data to all computers
destination MAC Address is FF-FF-FF-FF-FF-FF it says this is a broadcast address, every computer that is looking for a packet will say, im looking for this chunck of data send me your mac address

Broadcast Domain - 
    Any time you have a group of computers that can hear each other's broadcast you are in a broadcast domain.

Quick Review
    - Unicast Transmission is addressed to a single device on a network
    - a broadcast transmission is sent to every device in a broadcast domain.
    - a broadcast addess looks like this: FF-FF-FF-FF-FF-FF